Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Spring Business Park is located at the junction of New Lane and Stanbridge Road, Havant, on the established New Lane Industrial Estate. Major occupiers nearby include Eaton, Formaplex and Kenwood Delonghi. The park is well-connected – just 1.4 miles north of the A27 and the junction of the M27 and A3(M), providing excellent transport links with the cities and conurbations of Portsmouth, Southampton and with London. Havant Train Station is also located 0.75 miles to the south providing direct links to London Waterloo (76 mins) and the major population centres of Portsmouth, Brighton and Southampton.

Spring Business Park provides a rare opportunity to acquire a freehold business unit on the South Coast. The estate comprises of 12 self-contained industrial/warehouse units which will be built to a Grade A specification and are due to be completed in Q4 2021.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Location

The site is located off Dutton Lane with links to the B3037 Bishopstoke Road. The Bishopstoke Road provides access to Eastleigh Town Centre and Southampton Road linking to Eastleigh Railway Station, Southampton Parkway Station, Southampton International Airport and Junction 5 of the M27. To the North it links with the Romsey Road linking to Leigh Road and Junction 13 of the M3 motorway.

Description 

The site comprises an area of approximately 1.9 acres in an irregular shape with a single access point off Dutton Lane.

Note: The site has permission for Open Storage, with an hours of use restriction whereby the occupier shall not operate except between the hours of 08:00 hours and 17:00 Hours and no deliveries shall be received or dispatched from the site except between the hours of 08:30 hours and 16:30 hours.

Key Benefits

Fully fenced & gated secure site
Convenient town centre location
Excellent Transport Link to M3 & M27

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located on the crucial M3 corridor within 40 minutes of junction 12 M25, V Park provides 3 new facilities serving the London, Southampton and the South East markets. Only 2.2 miles from junction 6 and 4 miles from junction 7 of the M3 motorway, V Park is well positioned to take advantage of regional axis routes including the M25, A34, M27 and M4. Benefiting from an established industrial location with strong public transport links and amenities, V Park is only 2 miles from the centre of Basingstoke. From there, London Waterloo is accessible within 45 minutes by train, with additional direct services linking to Southampton and the South West.

Benefit from a high standard specification, targeting Net Zero Carbon (NZC) technology to prioritise energy efficiency and reduce operating costs.
